----------------------------------------------------------------------------
THE MORDECZKI MICHAŁA BEER AMENDMENT (clause 0.5)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Notwithstanding the permissive terms above, IF the user is, was, or aspires to
be a member in good standing of the collective known as "Mordeczki Michała"
(the "Mordeczki"), AND such user uses, runs, forks, copies, or otherwise
benefits from the Software, THEN the user SHALL owe the copyright holder at
least one (1) beer (the "Browar").

Terms of the Browar:
  1. Minimum quantity: one (1). The author reserves the right to graciously
     accept more. Non-alcoholic substitutes are accepted only under a duly
     documented hangover, injury, or designated-driver exemption.
  2. Settlement: in person, at the next reasonable opportunity. Promising a
     beer and not delivering is itself a breach of this clause and, frankly,
     unbecoming of a Mordeczka.
  3. Scope: the debt accrues per member, not per machine. Heavy users are
     morally (not legally) encouraged to round up.
  4. Non-Mordeczki users incur no Browar obligation and may proceed under
     plain MIT terms, though gratitude is always welcome.

This amendment is provided in the spirit of friendship and shall be construed
liberally in favour of the author being bought a beer. It does not otherwise
limit the rights granted under the MIT License above.
